data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code in EF Core 10:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile**. Replace it with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, etc. — the parameter is now `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`.

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified / use full path

**Two sub-changes:**

| Scenario | EF Core 9 column | EF Core 10 column |
|----------|-------------------|---------------------|
| `ShippingAddress.Street` + `BillingAddress.Street` | Both → `Street` (silent collision!) | `Street` and `Street1` |
| `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` (nested) | `BillingAddress_City` | `Payment_BillingAddress_City` |

**Fix** — pin existing column names explicitly if you have an existing database:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// Nested: pin old name if needed
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City"); // old convention
```

Or generate a new migration and let EF rename the columns (review the migration carefully).

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Add `string logCommandText` as the last parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter (redacted SQL for logs)
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

The same parameter was added to `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, `CommandScalarExecuted`, `CommandNonQueryExecuting`, and `CommandNonQueryExecuted`.
